  "Antoine Lavoisier is known as the father of modern chemistry and established the law of conservation of mass through precise measurements during chemical reactions.": "",
  "According to the law of conservation of mass, what happens to the total mass during a chemical reaction in a closed system?": "",
  "It increases slightly each time": "",
  "It decreases slightly each time": "",
  "It remains exactly the same": "",
  "It doubles during the reaction": "",
  "The law of conservation of mass states that mass is neither created nor destroyed in a chemical reaction, so the total mass of reactants equals the total mass of products.": "",
